Steps to install Grafana in Ubuntu and Debian(64 Bit)SHA256: 5bbf5f7517ec89b87fc3550cb05827383af68358763c15aee516b90a46cff707
sudo apt-get install -y adduser libfontconfig1 musl
wget https://dl.grafana.com/grafana-enterprise/release/12.3.2/grafana-enterprise_12.3.2_21390657659_linux_amd64.deb
sudo dpkg -i grafana-enterprise_12.3.2_21390657659_linux_amd64.deb


sudo /bin/systemctl daemon-reload
sudo /bin/systemctl enable grafana-server
sudo /bin/systemctl start grafana-server

By default grafana running on the port number 3000

username: admin
password: admin 

setup new password for it

Step 2: Create a Datasource for monitoring the Github Account Repository:

Grafana --> Data Sources --> find more data source plugins --> Github --> Install

After installing the plugin  &  Create a token in the Github Repo with below permissions:
--> repo
--> admin:org --> read:org
--> admin:repo_hook --> read:repo_hook
--> user --> read:user & user:email
--> admin:enterprise --> read:enterprise
--> audit_log --> read:audit_log
--> project --> read:project   & generate token with these permissions


Now Create a Data Source in the Grafana 
- Add Data source --> select Github --> Give name or default name is also fine 
- Remain default settings & 
- Connection through PAT(Personal Access Token) 
- Additional Settings --> Github License --> Basic or Enterprize (select one) --> Save & test

& 

Now Create a Dashboard Manauly or Import with the ID
=====================================================
Below is the link to import the Dashboard with ID: 
https://grafana.com/grafana/dashboards/14000-github-default/

Copy the ID & Go to Dashboard in Grafana & Click on Import & Paste the ID in (Find & import dashboards for common applications at grafana.com/dashboards:) --> Load

Importing dashboard from Grafana.com
Options --> Name: DevOps_Github_Repo
Github --> Select the Github Data Source  --> Import

Note: By Deafult we did not get the Github Data 
 * We need to select our Github by aading the Datasource & Organization name or Github Username & Repository & Branch(For EX: main) & select Duration of Time.

